main event: The observer sighted a flickering light that later appeared to be two points of light which remained stationary for approximately 10 minutes in the northwest sky.
interesting points: The witness was requested to complete an AF Form 117 but has not done so as yet.
The observer states that the object did not appear to be a helicopter.
The sighting occurred in Kettering, Ohio.
The conclusion of the report was 'possible aircraft (helicopter)'.
The report includes sketches of the observed phenomenon.
